frameDefinitions: A Theme is in a stable position with respect to a Location.
A group of Individuals form a group, the Entourage, which remains co-located with the Attended_person.
This frame has to do with people (the Residents) residing in Locations, sometimes with a Co-resident.
An Entity is presented as having been seen or experienced by a (typically generic and backgrounded)
An Agent supports their body in a particular Location.
frameExamples: Our offices are <t>located</t> about two miles south of I-85 .
Just before eleven o'clock, one of the consultants came to do a ward round, followed by his <t><fex name='ent'>entourage</fex></t> of junior doctors and medical students.
Susanna Fulton's work is <t>new</t> to me.
listRoleDefinitions: An entity which is at a particular Location
A salient entity that the <fen>Theme</fen> is located with respect to.
The time at which the <fen>Theme</fen> is at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The location (generally presumed to be known to the interlocutor) with respect to which the location of the <fen>Theme</fen> can be understood.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Entourage</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that follow the Attended.
The individual(s) that reside at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The place in which somebody resides.
A person or group of people that the resident is staying with or among.
This role refers to the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Resident</fen> resides.
A concrete thing or abstract phenomenon or fact that is assessed in terms of how well recognizable it is to a <fen>Cognizer</fen>.
The (typically non-specific and backgrounded) sentient being for whom the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses a specified level of recognizability.
The deviation of the actual level of recognizability of the <fen>Entity</fen> from the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual whose body is in a particular posture.  The <fen>Agent</fen> role is generally expressed as the external argument of verbs:
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen>.  The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Agent</fen> is frequently expressed and generally occurs as a PP Complement:
The part of the body that provides support to the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body in the posture.
This role indicates the Time interval during which the <fen>Agent</fen> held a certain posture.
listRoleExamples: Just before eleven o'clock, one of the consultants came to do a ward round, followed by his entourage <fex>of junior doctors and medical students</fex>.
Most of the large <fex><t>entourage</t></fex> the president had brought with him quietly left him.
<fex>The lord's</fex> train consisted of several dozen servants, cooks, and other attendants.
He gave <fex>an address</fex> quite familiar to the chauffeur.
The information used to illustrate the concept is familiar <fex>to the reader</fex>.
He gave an address <fex>quite</fex> familiar to the chauffeur.
I stood <fex>on my heels</fex> and looked out the window
<fex>Yesterday evening</fex> he was sitting in his armchair as usual
